      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nHi Wally,\n\nIn your words \"It was originally designed for Cray's DVS but not worked and not used by DVS in production\", does it mean that DVS can use lnet as communication layer but need not this patch's feature, or does it mean DVS cannot run over lnet protocol now?\n\nWe are interesting with DVS such I/O forwarding things.\n\nThanks,\nXuezhao",
